<jdudley@eaicorp.com>
[My assumption was that, since the Indonesian authorities had decided not to
pursue their investigations into the source of the avian influenza infections
in Jakarta, they did not place much reliance on the veracity of the H5-
positive reaction obtained with faeces from the bird cage. Dr. Dudley has a
fair point; it does depend on the reliability of detecting avian influenza
virus antigen/genome in bird faeces. Perhaps another correspondent can
enlighten us? - Mod.CP]
